      • setOrder

        public void setOrder(double order)
        Sets the oder.

        The order attribute is an optional attribute of type Double. It is there to handle the case where compartments in a layout overlap, and tools want to clearly disambiguate which CompartmentGlyph is on top of the other. The order attribute follows the coordinate system. There are z dimension points into a screen; thus, an element with a lower order value will be in front of an elements with a higher value. If not specified, the order is undefined and tools are free to display the compartment glyphs in the order that best fits their needs.

        Note: if z coordinates are used (and this order is seemingly redundant), the order can still be used to disambiguate drawing order.
